The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to felony theft (>$2500-$500), contrary to Section 943.20(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes, a Class I felony.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge. Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) No contact with Harvey Clark or his residence;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, work search or combination;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) pay balance of restitution in the amount of $2,625.31 to Havey Clark at 1819 19th Street, Two Rivers, WI;
7) spend twenty (20) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 10-07-14 by 6:00 p.m.;
8) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge.
